RAF WATCH

Interactive map of UK Royal Air Force activity using ADS-B data.

Hex codes are scraped from live-mobile-mode-s.eu. Flight traces
are fetched from globe.adsbexchange.com (tar1090 format) and
stored in a DuckDB cache and exported as compact binary files
(RAF1 format), parsed client-side. The frontend is static
HTML/CSS/JS with MapLibre GL.

Setup

  uv run scripts/scrape_hex.py             Scrape hex codes
  uv run scripts/fetch_adsb.py             Fetch last 14 days of traces
  uv run scripts/fetch_adsb.py --days 7    Fetch last 7 days
  uv run scripts/fetch_bases.py            Fetch RAF base locations from OSM
  python -m http.server -d web             Serve and open localhost:8000

The fetch script caches results in data/cache.duckdb and is
resumable. Each day's data is exported as a separate .bin file
loaded on demand by the date slider. Hours flown per day are
included in the manifest (data/manifest.json).

Binary format — RAF1 (per-day .bin files)

  File header:
    [4 bytes]    magic "RAF1"
    [uint32 LE]  day epoch (UTC midnight as unix timestamp)
    [uint16 LE]  flight count

  Per flight:
    [uint24 LE]  ICAO hex code
    [uvarint]    trace point count

    Per trace point (delta-encoded from previous, initial = 0):
      [uvarint]   dt (seconds)
      [svarint]   dlat (units of 1e-5 degrees)
      [svarint]   dlon (units of 1e-5 degrees)
      [svarint]   dalt (units of 25 ft; -1 = ground)
      [svarint]   dspeed (knots)
      [uint8]     track (degrees * 256/360)

  Varints use LEB128 (unsigned) and ZigZag + LEB128 (signed).

Manifest format (data/manifest.json)

  {"2026-02-21": 129.3, "2026-02-22": 75.1, ...}

  Keys are dates with .bin files, values are hours flown.

Data sources

  Hex codes    https://live-mobile-mode-s.eu/overviewall.php?DGCountry=UK
  Traces       https://globe.adsbexchange.com/globe_history/
  Bases        OpenStreetMap via Overpass API (military=airfield)
